#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:19
msgid "legal.privacy.thirdParty.ai"
msgstr "AI recognition: when you actively use AI recognition to add subscriptions, pasted text, uploaded images, and existing tag names are sent to the third-party AI platform configured in Settings."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:7
msgid "legal.privacy.intro"
msgstr "Renewlet does not inject external scripts by default. An instance operator can provide one external script through environment configuration; when you use a deployed instance, that script and its data handling are the operator's responsibility, which may be yours."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:26
msgid "legal.terms.intro"
msgstr "Renewlet (renewlet) is an open-source subscription management tool. This page explains the basic rules you should understand when using this project or a deployed instance."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:10
msgid "legal.privacy.data.business"
msgstr "Application data: subscriptions, category/payment/currency configuration, user settings, and related SQLite data."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:28
msgid "legal.terms.scope.lawful"
msgstr "You may use this project, including self-hosted deployments, as long as your use is lawful and compliant."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:22
msgid "legal.privacy.control.settings"
msgstr "You can change notification channel settings or disable notifications from Settings at any time."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:29
msgid "legal.terms.scope.accuracy"
msgstr "You are responsible for the accuracy of subscription, price, exchange-rate, and related data you enter. The project only provides management and display features."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:6
msgid "legal.privacy.subtitle"
msgstr "Last updated: 2026-01-12"

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:25
msgid "legal.terms.subtitle"
msgstr "Last updated: 2026-01-12"

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:38
msgid "legal.terms.disclaimer.loss"
msgstr "You are responsible for any loss caused by using this project or a deployed instance."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:17
msgid "legal.privacy.thirdParty.icons"
msgstr "Icon search: external favicon/logo candidates may be loaded in the browser as a fallback, with graceful fallback on failure."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:32
msgid "legal.terms.account.operator"
msgstr "If you use an instance operated by someone else, understand that the operator may have server and database administration access."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:23
msgid "legal.privacy.control.selfHost"
msgstr "If you self-host the deployment, you can manage, back up, or delete data through the PocketBase admin UI and `/pb_data`."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:24
msgid "legal.terms.title"
msgstr "Terms of Service"

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:37
msgid "legal.terms.disclaimer.asIs"
msgstr "The project is provided as is, without warranties of any kind, including accuracy, timeliness, or fitness for a particular purpose."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:31
msgid "legal.terms.account.localAuth"
msgstr "The project uses local authentication by default. Data is stored in SQLite and the local upload directory."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:16
msgid "legal.privacy.thirdParty.rates"
msgstr "Exchange rates: Exchange API or FloatRates JSON Feeds can be used for rate data, with the other remote source tried before built-in fallback rates."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:13
msgid "legal.privacy.usage.core"
msgstr "To provide core features: subscription management, statistics, calendar views, and personalized settings."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:14
msgid "legal.privacy.usage.notifications"
msgstr "For optional notifications: when notification channels are enabled, notification content is sent to the third-party channels you configure."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:35
msgid "legal.terms.thirdParty.responsibility"
msgstr "Availability, rate limits, and data accuracy of third-party services are the responsibility of those services."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:9
msgid "legal.privacy.data.account"
msgstr "Account data: managed by PocketBase authentication, such as email and local tokens."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:11
msgid "legal.privacy.data.files"
msgstr "Resource files: uploaded Logo/Icon images and similar files stored locally."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:18
msgid "legal.privacy.thirdParty.notifications"
msgstr "Notifications: Telegram, WeCom, Webhook, SMTP email, Bark, ServerChan, and similar channels receive the notification content you configure."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:34
msgid "legal.terms.thirdParty.features"
msgstr "Some features request third-party services, such as exchange-rate APIs, notification channels, and icon search sites."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:20
msgid "legal.privacy.thirdParty.customScript"
msgstr "Operator-provided script: an instance operator can provide one external script through environment configuration; that script may send visit data to its provider."

#. js-lingui-explicit-id
#: src/i18n/descriptors/legal.ts:5
msgid "legal.privacy.title"
msgstr "Privacy Policy"
